org.opentosca.toscana.plugins.cloudformation

Class CloudFormationLifecycle

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opentosca.toscana.core.plugin.lifecycle.AbstractLifecycle
      • org.opentosca.toscana.plugins.cloudformation.CloudFormationLifecycle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TransformationLifecycle, LifecycleAccess

    public class CloudFormationLifecycle
extends AbstractLifecycle
    Implements the AbstractLifecycle for the CloudFormationPlugin. It creates a CloudFormationModule and is able to perform the lifecycle operations.

      • checkModel

        public boolean checkModel()
        Performs the checkModel() lifecycle operation.
        The implementation of TransformationLifecycle.checkModel().
        Using the CheckModelNodeVisitor and the CheckModelRelationshipVisitor every node and relationship in the EffectiveModel is visited.
        Returns:
        if every found type is accepted return true

      • prepare

        public void prepare()
        Performs the prepare() lifecycle operation.
        The implementation of TransformationLifecycle.prepare().
        Using the PrepareModelNodeVisitor and the PrepareModelRelationshipVisitor every node and relationship in the EffectiveModel is visited. Compute nodes are visited first.

      • transform

        public void transform()
        Performs the transform() lifecycle operation.
        The implementation of TransformationLifecycle.transform().
        Using the TransformModelNodeVisitor every node in the EffectiveModel is visited. Compute nodes are visited first. Also environment variables which will appear in the transformed model are handled. The main artifact of the transformation, the CloudFormation template is created. Using the CloudFormationFileCreator all necessary scripts for the deployment are created.

      • cleanup

        public void cleanup()
        Performs the cleanup() lifecycle operation.
        The implementation of TransformationLifecycle.cleanup() does nothing.
